OL,6,F"If the pursuit of that becomes self-
OL,7,Fserving, it's a really problematic
OL,8,Findicator.
OL,10,F"We ask a lot of people and many of
OL,11,Four officers work excess hours, long
OL,12,Fhours, and are rewarded for that, and
OL,13,Fshould be rewarded for it.
OL,15,F"But if you really drill into who your
OL,16,Ftop overtime earners are, this is part
OL,17,Fof the Al Capone approach, you will
OL,18,Ffind people whose performance does not
OL,19,Fmatch the amount of money they're
